	   <a name=101243755970792></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101243755970792><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=101243755970792>RE: duelling SK's</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=101243755970792#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=80975><span id= >Ishkur</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>89 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jan 30th 7:39 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.20]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm sorry, but to be quite honest with you, this post on duelin' a Shadowknight is highly, highly flawed.&nbsp;&nbsp;No Shadowknight fights the same, so in order to fight a Shadowknight, you have to go in there expectin' anythin' and ev'rythin'.  Slipkin in this case left a lot of thin's hangin' and took a lot of thin's for granted and personally, if he fought a GOOD Shadowknight he'd be in a world of hurt.<br><br>For starters, a GOOD Shadowknight will use Harm Touch either A) As the killin' blow or B) When the tide of the fight is changin'.  You know, that 3rd and 10 that you NEED to make the first down on.  That's where Harm Touch comes into play.  It can be resisted, but you're gonna need some REALLY high resist so your best bet is to just brace yourself for it.  Hell, a GREAT Shadowknight can take you out WITHOUT it.  And it can be done.  Beware the Harm Touch.<br><br>The Shadowknight's pets are not a threat when it comes to damage.  But they will make your life a livin' hell.  They're just a nuisance.  Don't worry about the dual wield either.  Worry about the fact that they can bash.  Bein' stunned is somethin' that you don't wanna deal with.  Also, here's where the Blind Poison will not work.  The Blind Poison works like a spell.  It's not contact and inject.  The spell meter comes out and you have to wait til the poison &quot;casts&quot;.  Problem, if you get interrupted, you LOSE the poison and it doesn't connect.  Blind poisons against any class with pets....just...suck.<br><br>The biggest and most surprisin' thin' that has been forgotten in the SK battle is his/her ability to cast Fear on you.  Basically you will need High Resist for this especially.  If you are feared, you're in SERIOUS trouble because you can't do anythin' except get hit with shields, swords, maces, and spells.  Plus Fear interrupts your Pumice Stone castin', so get high resist for avoidin' to be feared.<br><br>And forget Evade because although it may drop his target, it won't drop the pets target.  Remember, the Pet is an NPC so it's also a way of keepin' you from hidin'.  Pretty nasty and unfair, eh?  Get used to it, because it's not good.  <br><br>Spells are a pain too.  You get hit with excessive DoT's and you're gonna be panickin'.  And I think we all know the effects of Engulfin' and Doomin' Darkness but in case you don't, it's a Snare + DoT.  Lifetaps are nasty cuz you will not interrupt those.  They're too fast.  It's hard to cancel out anythin' when you're DoTed and you got someone hittin' you constantly, whether it's a 2hs, 1hs, or a pet tappin' at you.  And of course, the Shadowknights favorite spell, Shadowstep.  Basically this spell teleports the Shadowknight about a good amount of feet away from you.  It serves for an escape when they're losin', plus it gives that person some room to cast a spell, fear most likely. <br><br>So here's how you fight a Shadowknight.  Be slick and get buffed but no matter if you can't get buffs, you can't get buffs.  S'all good, here's what ya do.<br><br>1) Poison is good.  Weakenin' poison, Direct Damage, or Mana poisons are good.  Stick to those.  Commit to either or.  If you're gonna sap Strength, try to keep yourself alive by fightin' hard and movin' a lot.  Direct damage, raise hell in battle.  Mana poison, well, try to have enough resist til he runs outta mana.  Then it's straight up fightin'<br><br>2) Brace yourself for the Harm Touch.  It can come at any time.  Try to keep yourself so that HT doesn't kill you or remove your momentum.<br><br>3) Instill Doubt is your best friend. Use it! This will prevent him from fightin' so you can have enough time to land damage and/or give you time to poison.<br><br>4) Keep movin'.  If he has a slow 2hs, stick and move.  If it's 1hs, he's gonna have a shield for AC.  Expect faster hits and try to disarm when possible.<br><br>5) Hit fast enough so he doesn't cast.  Watch for Shadowstep and the moment he fades, look around and pounce at the most opportune time.<br><br>6) Do your best to stay alive, don't quit and most importantly, don't let him take you out of your strategy.  If you give it your all and stick to what you do best, he may panic and do somethin' stupid.  That's where you catch him.<br><br>7) If you have Pumice Stones, use 2 charges on Disepllin' HIM.  A smart Shadowknight will cast some form of See Invis or Self Buff or whatever.  Strip him bare.  If you do that, THEN you can utilize your Hidin' and Sneakin', especially when he snaps out from fear.<br><br>If you do all these thin's and stick to your game, then your chances are really high.  Might be tougher facin' an Ogre or Troll Shadowknight, but hell you can do it.  Just fight your ass off.<br>&nbsp;<br>Formerly Ishkur D`Macbain<br>Now...Ishkur Leroux<br>Teir'Dal Dobluth<br><br>"So what if I stabbed him in the back.&nbsp;&nbsp;His back was to me!"</td></tr>
