	   <tr><td colspan=2>Coming from a long history in first-person shooters, the EQ control setup was completely unacceptable to me as well. You can change all the keys around as you want by going into the keyboard menu in options. I suggest switching to the 'WASD' setup as follows: set forward to 'w', left to 'a', right to 'd', back to 's', attack to 'q', backstab (which coincidentally was user hotkey 2 for me too) to 'e', and duck to 'x'. Or you can set the backstab to somewhere near the numpad, like the numpad '+' or something. Circle-strafe CAN work on melee mobs, as long as you have a little help. Get something that can stun: weapon proc, poison, basher, caster, or whatever, and you can make the fight much quicker. Unfortunately, the mob is always faster than you if you try to get around it without help. There was one time I think I successfully backstabbed a mob I was soloing, but only because of lag. <br><br>Lag backstabs YOU for 32000 damage!<br>You have been slain by Lag!<br>LOADING, PLEASE WAIT...<br><br>Heh, I remember this board discussing what EQLizer had to say about rogues. After many laughs (&quot;I cannot see a dwarf or barbarian being a successful rogue&quot;) and a few misunderstandings, we determined it was pretty much only useful if you're on a PvP server, or you're planning on soloing. Otherwise, it's DEX&gt;STR&gt;AGI&gt;STA&gt;whatever for me. If you ever hear someone say it's hard to find DEX or AGI equipment, they're either lying or misinformed (serpentine bracers, anyone?). I have 162 DEX un-twinked. And most of my DEX stuff has AGI as well, giving me 120 AGI. <br><br>LOL; barbs are big enough they can hide in their own shadow (and stupid enough to believe they can), so it works :).<br>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD (Retired)<br>32nd Dwarf Rogue<br>Lords of Belterra<br>Xegony</td></tr>
