	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, here is some advice for rogues, for the strategies that non rogues use against you.<br><br>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;The first thing when dueling a rogue, is NEVER EVER EVER STAND STILL EXCEPT TO CAST A SPELL.  Standing in one place is asking to be backstabbed.  A rogue who can't backstab is a dead rogue.<br>2.  Next, NUKE WHEN THE TIME IS RIGHT.  If a rogue hides while you are casting a nuke, it will still hit him.  Even though he will not be targeted, the nuke will still hit him and break his hide.<br>3.  FIGHT ON YOUR OWN TERMS.  The biggest advantage a rogue has is a small, compact space in an Arena.  Fight outside, in the hills.<br>4.  HAVE SOW, WILL TRAVEL  Get a sow, you'll need it.  Trust me.<br>5.  KITE.  Rogues hate it when people kite them.  Any rogue that complains to a ranger about &quot;kiting too much&quot; should be kited.  Any rogue who complains to a ranger about &quot;not being fair&quot; should be kited.  Any rogue who duels a ranger should DEFINITELY be kited.  And hit with my TRUESHOT if you ask me.  And nuked.  And then hit with my weapon.  And kicked.  And kited.  And nuked.  And rooted.  And snared.  And KILLED!<br>LoL, jk guys, i gave up my rogue, but I still have what it takes to know a rogue.<br>In fact, ANYONE who duels my ranger should be rooted, kited, hit with my TRUESHOT, nuked and snared.<br>Hope this helps you in duels, now you know what non rogues will try to do.<br>JimThayner<br>Catterbe, 18 Ranger<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
