	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 24th 8:42 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.05]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you are going to duel casters there are a few things to keep in mind:<br><br>1) fight the caster and not the pet<br>2) use blinding poisons<br>3) get high MR gear to keep roots from sticking<br>4) use mana drain poisons<br>5) Wizards and Magicians tend to use elemental spells.&nbsp;&nbsp;Get your  Fire and Cold resist up against them.  Necros use poison based and magic based spells, mostly. Get your resists up against them.  Chanters use straight magic mostly so get MR up against them.<br>6) use more blind poisons<br>7) if you run from a caster in a fight you give up the only advantage you have - melee damage. You will likely die<br>8) use mana drain poisons<br>9) most spells have a cast time over 2 seconds. Use weapons that have a 20 delay or lower. You will interrupt casting more reliably.  Even though the weapon does less damage per hit you will, against lightly armored mages, do more damage over time.<br>10) use more mana drain poisons<br>11) get some form of device that allows you to cancell magic.  Damage shields are a real nuisance.  High resists help soften them but only a cancel magic really does the job.<br>12) use even more mana drain poisons.<br><br>A rogue is most effective when he/she can choose the time and conditions for the fight.  Think like an assassin and not a street brawler.  Don't duel someone unless you have prepared to duel that person well in advance and have the proper tools on your person.  On PVP servers this can't always be helped.  In that case get MR up to avoid roots and run away.  You can come back and nail the jerk later when he/she is medding and not being well guarded.  Never fight unless the odds are heavily tipped in your favor.  Is that fair? No, but you are a rogue. What do you care about fair?<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jan 24 10:51:35 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
