	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well from my duelin' experience, it comes down to a lot of thin's.&nbsp;&nbsp;First off, when fightin' pure casters, you gotta have this motto, &quot;If you hit him, he can't cast.&quot;  That's what it comes down too.  With Rogue speed in weapons, you're not gonna allow him or her to cast.<br><br>It is pretty hard at lower lvls but I've done it.  At higher levels, I've taken out Necros and Enchanters but it's always a mission.  They RELY on Root or Pets, but if you focus your attention on them, they panic and that's when you strike.  Trust me, when you backstab, they WILL feel it.  'sides, if you're rooted, use those arrows or those throwin' knives to your advantage.  There's always a way.  You can't give in.<br>&nbsp;<br>Formerly Ishkur D`Macbain<br>Now...Ishkur Leroux<br>Teir'Dal Dobluth<br><br>"So what if I stabbed him in the back.&nbsp;&nbsp;His back was to me!"</td></tr>
